every day with her patient...

749
00:43:42,453 --> 00:43:45,422
Dr. Fletcher takes him
for a cautious outing...

750
00:43:45,456 --> 00:43:49,756
an afternoon at her sister's
house in nearby Teaneck.

751
00:43:49,793 --> 00:43:51,920
Meryl Fletcher
is an aviatrix...

752
00:43:51,962 --> 00:43:53,930
a fine professional pilot.

753
00:43:53,964 --> 00:43:56,933
Eudora Fletcher
is an amateur pilot...

754
00:43:56,967 --> 00:43:59,435
and the afternoon
is spent relaxing...

755
00:43:59,470 --> 00:44:02,337
and retelling
old flying experiences.

756
00:44:03,907 --> 00:44:05,875
As the weeks pass...

757
00:44:05,909 --> 00:44:09,367
Zelig is encouraged
to open up more and more...

758
00:44:09,413 --> 00:44:11,381
to give his own opinions.

759
00:44:11,415 --> 00:44:14,384
What was guarded at first
soon becomes expansive.

760
00:44:14,418 --> 00:44:18,946
I hated my stepmother.
I don't care who knows it.

761
00:44:20,958 --> 00:44:22,425
I love baseball.

762
00:44:22,459 --> 00:44:24,927
It doesn't
have to mean anything.

763
00:44:24,962 --> 00:44:27,453
It's just very beautiful
to watch.

764
00:44:29,600 --> 00:44:33,934
I'm a Democrat.
I always was a Democrat.

765
00:44:35,472 --> 00:44:40,432
Is it OK if I don't agree
with you about that recording?

766
00:44:40,477 --> 00:44:42,445
Of course.

767
00:44:42,479 --> 00:44:46,609
Brahms is just always
too melodramatic for me.

768
00:44:46,650 --> 00:44:49,448
You have to be
your own person...

769
00:44:49,486 --> 00:44:51,954
and make your own
moral choices...

770
00:44:51,989 --> 00:44:54,958
even when they do
require real courage.

771
00:44:54,992 --> 00:44:59,156
Otherwise, you're like
a robot or a lizard.

772
00:44:59,196 --> 00:45:01,892
Are you really going
to marry that lawyer?

773
00:45:01,932 --> 00:45:04,423
I would much rather you didn't.

774
00:45:05,936 --> 00:45:07,403
I don't agree.

775
00:45:07,438 --> 00:45:10,430
I think this guy Mussolini
is a loser.

776
00:45:12,443 --> 00:45:16,209
Are we ever going to make love?

777
00:45:16,246 --> 00:45:17,873
It has been three months...

778
00:45:17,915 --> 00:45:20,884
and the board wishes
to examine the patient.

779
00:45:20,918 --> 00:45:24,877
Dr. Fletcher says Zelig isn't
ready to leave the premises.

780
00:45:24,922 --> 00:45:27,390
The doctors agree
to visit him there.

781
00:45:27,424 --> 00:45:30,393
The date is set...
four days hence.

782
00:45:30,427 --> 00:45:32,395
If progress is insufficient...

783
00:45:32,429 --> 00:45:34,420
she will be removed
from the case.

784
00:45:36,500 --> 00:45:39,958
I was very nervous
because in his waking state...

785
00:45:40,003 --> 00:45:42,972
he never remembered anything
from his trance state...

786
00:45:43,006 --> 00:45:45,474
and I wondered
if there could be some way...

787
00:45:45,509 --> 00:45:47,977
of locking
these two things together.

788
00:45:48,011 --> 00:45:50,479
And then I also was worried...

789
00:45:50,514 --> 00:45:53,483
that if he was
with strong personalities...

790
00:45:53,517 --> 00:45:55,712
he might lose his personality.

791
00:45:55,753 --> 00:45:58,051
Sunday at noon,
the doctors arrive.

792
00:45:58,088 --> 00:46:00,556
They are greeted
by Eudora Fletcher...

793
00:46:00,591 --> 00:46:04,550
and Leonard Zelig and are shown
around the grounds.

794
00:46:04,595 --> 00:46:07,564
Though Dr. Fletcher
is tense and alert...

795
00:46:07,598 --> 00:46:10,567
Leonard Zelig seems calm
and at ease.

796
00:46:10,601 --> 00:46:14,059
Despite the fact that he
is surrounded by physicians...

797
00:46:14,104 --> 00:46:16,572
he does not turn into one.

798
00:46:16,607 --> 00:46:19,576
The encounter appears to be
a resounding success...

799
00:46:19,610 --> 00:46:22,078
when Dr. Henry Mayerson
comments innocently...

800
00:46:22,112 --> 00:46:26,071
about the weather,
saying that it is a nice day.

801
00:46:26,116 --> 00:46:29,574
Zelig tells Dr. Mayerson
that he does not agree...

802
00:46:29,620 --> 00:46:32,088
that it is a nice day.

803
00:46:32,122 --> 00:46:34,090
Dr. Mayerson is taken aback...

804
00:46:34,124 --> 00:46:36,524
at the firmness
of Zelig's conviction.

805
00:46:36,560 --> 00:46:41,520
He points out that the sun
is shining and that it is mild.

806
00:46:41,565 --> 00:46:45,023
Zelig, trained to voice his own
personal opinions fearlessly...

807
00:46:45,068 --> 00:46:47,036
is too aggressive.

808
00:46:47,070 --> 00:46:51,029
He has been molded too far
in the other direction.

809
00:46:51,074 --> 00:46:53,042
He has become
over-opinionated...

810
00:46:53,076 --> 00:46:57,012
and cannot brook any
disagreement with his own views.

811
00:46:57,047 --> 00:47:00,574
I'd taken him too far
in the other direction.

812
00:47:00,617 --> 00:47:03,586
He struck Dr. Mayerson
and several board members...

813
00:47:03,620 --> 00:47:05,087
with a rake.

814
00:47:05,122 --> 00:47:07,090
This wasn't what we wanted...

815
00:47:07,124 --> 00:47:09,490
yet I felt I'd
accomplished something.

816
00:47:09,526 --> 00:47:12,552
If I could have him
two more weeks...

817
00:47:12,596 --> 00:47:15,064
I could do some fine-tuning...

818
00:47:15,098 --> 00:47:18,192
and turn Leonard Zelig
back into his own man.

819
00:47:28,679 --> 00:47:32,046
Dr. Eudora Nesbit Fletcher,
the hero...

820
00:47:32,082 --> 00:47:34,050
or should we say, heroine...
of the hour.

821
00:47:34,084 --> 00:47:36,484
The beautiful and brilliant
young psychiatrist...

822
00:47:36,520 --> 00:47:38,988
never lost faith
in her conviction...

823
00:47:39,022 --> 00:47:40,990
that Leonard Zelig,
the human chameleon...

824
00:47:41,024 --> 00:47:42,992
was suffering
from a mental disorder.

825
00:47:43,026 --> 00:47:44,459
Working with her cousin...

826
00:47:44,494 --> 00:47:47,088
cameraman Paul Deghuee,
the doctor managed...

827
00:47:47,130 --> 00:47:49,098
to keep a vital record
of the proceedings...

828
00:47:49,132 --> 00:47:52,499
including rare footage
of Zelig hypnotized.

829
00:47:52,536 --> 00:47:55,562
The patient and healer
have become fast friends...

830
00:47:55,606 --> 00:47:57,574
and enjoy
one another's company...

831
00:47:57,608 --> 00:48:00,577
even when she's
not working on him.

832
00:48:00,611 --> 00:48:03,580
The result of maintaining
a minority opinion...

833
00:48:03,614 --> 00:48:05,707
is a resounding success
for psychiatry.

834
00:48:05,749 --> 00:48:08,912
Who says women
are just good for sewing?

835
00:48:08,952 --> 00:48:10,351
Now it's on to City Hall...

836
00:48:10,387 --> 00:48:12,355
where the town's
newest celebrities...

837
00:48:12,389 --> 00:48:14,084
are given the key to the city.

838
00:48:14,124 --> 00:48:16,024
We're honored to present...

839
00:48:16,059 --> 00:48:18,926
this key
to New York City to you.

840
00:48:21,565 --> 00:48:24,534
Jimmy Walker
did want to be here...

841
00:48:24,568 --> 00:48:29,062
and sing "Leonard the Lizard,"
but he was just too busy.

842
00:48:31,942 --> 00:48:34,035
After city hall,
Eudora Fletcher...

843
00:48:34,077 --> 00:48:36,477
the beautiful genius
who cured Zelig...

844
00:48:36,513 --> 00:48:38,481
of his science-defying
condition...

845
00:48:38,515 --> 00:48:42,474
is honored by fellow scientists
at New York's Waldorf-Astoria.

846
00:48:42,519 --> 00:48:45,488
Present are luminaries
from all over the world...

847
00:48:45,522 --> 00:48:48,491
not just in the field
of psychiatry...

848
00:48:48,525 --> 00:48:51,494
but physics, biology,
mathematics, and you name it.

849
00:48:51,528 --> 00:48:54,326
Here she is exchanging theories
with Nils Andersen...

850
00:48:54,364 --> 00:48:56,855
the father
of modern blood disease.

851
00:48:56,900 --> 00:48:59,425
Later in the week,
Dr. Fletcher is again honored...

852
00:48:59,469 --> 00:49:02,438
as she gets to christen
her first ship.

853
00:49:02,472 --> 00:49:05,373
Quite a success story
for a little girl...

854
00:49:05,409 --> 00:49:06,967
from the backwoods.

855
00:49:10,948 --> 00:49:12,415
I'm speaking to you...

856
00:49:12,449 --> 00:49:15,009
from the home of
Mrs. Catherine Fletcher.

857
00:49:15,052 --> 00:49:18,021
She's the mother
of Dr. Eudora Fletcher...

858
00:49:18,055 --> 00:49:21,024
the famous psychiatrist
in the news these days.

859
00:49:21,058 --> 00:49:25,017
I'll be asking Mrs. Fletcher...
to begin with...

860
00:49:25,062 --> 00:49:28,031
to tell us something
about what it's like...

861
00:49:28,065 --> 00:49:31,034
to raise a medical genius.

862
00:49:31,068 --> 00:49:34,037
I might ask you about
the many sacrifices...

863
00:49:34,071 --> 00:49:37,472
You've made to put your daughter
through medical school.

864
00:49:37,507 --> 00:49:39,975
Speak right into
the microphones, please.

865
00:49:40,010 --> 00:49:42,069
Sacrifices, we had none.

866
00:49:42,112 --> 00:49:45,479
John was a stockbroker.
We had plenty of money...

867
00:49:45,515 --> 00:49:47,983
and I came from a wealthy
Philadelphia family.

868
00:49:48,018 --> 00:49:51,818
I'm sure that your daughter
always wanted to be a doctor...

869
00:49:51,855 --> 00:49:53,982
ever since she could remember.

870
00:49:54,024 --> 00:49:55,992
I don't think so.

871
00:49:56,026 --> 00:49:59,484
I always thought she
wanted to be a flier...

872
00:49:59,529 --> 00:50:02,498
like her sister Meryl,
and raise a family...

873
00:50:02,532 --> 00:50:04,500
but she was a very moody child.

874
00:50:04,534 --> 00:50:07,503
But a mother always
dreams for her child...

875
00:50:07,537 --> 00:50:10,005
to have the success
your daughter has.

876
00:50:10,040 --> 00:50:12,508
She was a very difficult girl.

877
00:50:12,542 --> 00:50:14,510
Tell me about your husband.

878
00:50:14,544 --> 00:50:16,011
I understand that he is
a simple businessman.

879
00:50:16,046 --> 00:50:18,014
He must be so thrilled
and pleased...

880
00:50:18,048 --> 00:50:22,007
to have his daughter
achieve such recognition.

881
00:50:22,052 --> 00:50:25,510
John had problems... depression.
He drank.

882
00:50:25,555 --> 00:50:28,524
Well, Mrs. Fletcher,
thank you so much...

883
00:50:28,558 --> 00:50:31,391
for speaking with us today.

884
00:50:39,403 --> 00:50:41,928
Here at San Simeon,
glorious dreamland...

885
00:50:41,972 --> 00:50:44,566
of newspaper mogul
William Randolph Hearst...

886
00:50:44,608 --> 00:50:48,669
celebrities from all walks
of society sun or play.

887
00:50:48,712 --> 00:50:51,613
There's Marie Dressler
with Mr. Hearst.

888
00:50:51,648 --> 00:50:54,617
Always a popular guest
at San Simeon...

889
00:50:54,651 --> 00:50:58,610
Miss Dressler accepts a flower
from an ardent admirer.

890
00:50:58,655 --> 00:51:01,624
Along with her is Marion Davies.

891
00:51:01,658 --> 00:51:05,116
When she works, Miss Davies
is always dead serious...

892
00:51:05,162 --> 00:51:07,630
But here,
at this fabulous playground...

893
00:51:07,664 --> 00:51:10,656
She shows us her fun side.

894
00:51:10,700 --> 00:51:14,261
There she is with
you-know-who... Charlie Chaplin...

895
00:51:14,304 --> 00:51:16,363
always kidding.

896
00:51:16,406 --> 00:51:19,534
Although New York
is 3,000 miles away...

897
00:51:19,576 --> 00:51:23,444
Jimmy Walker appears through
Mr. Hearst's enchanted gateway.

898
00:51:23,480 --> 00:51:27,041
Another New Yorker
is Leonard Zelig...

899
00:51:27,084 --> 00:51:29,052
here shown clowning...

900
00:51:29,086 --> 00:51:31,554
with everybody's
favorite cowboy... Tom Mix.

901
00:51:31,588 --> 00:51:33,556
Won't Tony be jealous?

902
00:51:33,590 --> 00:51:36,320
Tony is Tom's horse...

903
00:51:36,359 --> 00:51:39,294
and we always thought
they went everywhere together.

904
00:51:39,329 --> 00:51:41,593
There's that fellow
Chaplin again...

905
00:51:41,631 --> 00:51:44,191
this time with Adolphe Menjou.

906
00:51:44,234 --> 00:51:48,466
There's Claire Windsor
and Delores del Rio...

907
00:51:48,505 --> 00:51:51,099
and a very charming
Eudora Fletcher...

908
00:51:51,141 --> 00:51:54,110
chatting with Hollywood's
newest dancing sensation...

909
00:51:54,144 --> 00:51:56,112
James Cagney.

910
00:51:56,146 --> 00:51:58,614
And what have we here?

911
00:51:58,648 --> 00:52:01,742
Only a beautiful lady
named Carole Lombard.

912
00:52:01,785 --> 00:52:04,151
There's Dr. Fletcher
and Leonard Zelig...

913
00:52:04,187 --> 00:52:08,647
hitting a few with Bobby Jones
on Mr. Hearst's golf course.

914
00:52:08,692 --> 00:52:12,651
Unless Leonard can go back to
his old chameleon personality...

915
00:52:12,696 --> 00:52:17,656
and turn into a golf pro,
I'd bet my money on Bobby.

916
00:52:17,701 --> 00:52:20,693
But who cares,
if they're having fun?

917
00:52:26,009 --> 00:52:31,072
Do you want to give the kids
of this country some advice?

918
00:52:31,114 --> 00:52:34,572
I sure do.
Kids, you got to be yourself.

919
00:52:34,618 --> 00:52:36,518
Don't act like anybody else...

920
00:52:36,553 --> 00:52:39,454
because you think
they have all the answers.

921
00:52:39,489 --> 00:52:43,585
Be your own man, speak up,
say what's on your mind.

922
00:52:43,627 --> 00:52:46,596
Maybe they can't do that
in foreign countries...

923
00:52:46,630 --> 00:52:48,598
but that's the American way.

924
00:52:48,632 --> 00:52:52,591
I used to be a member
of the reptile family...

925
00:52:52,636 --> 00:52:54,627
but I'm not anymore.

926
00:53:39,349 --> 00:53:42,785
Zelig, no longer a chameleon,
is his own man.

927
00:53:42,819 --> 00:53:46,277
His point of view
on politics, art, and love...

928
00:53:46,323 --> 00:53:49,292
is honest and direct.

929
00:53:49,326 --> 00:53:52,784
Though his taste is described
by many as lowbrow...

930
00:53:52,829 --> 00:53:54,797
it is his own.

931
00:53:54,831 --> 00:53:57,800
He is finally an individual,
a human being.

932
00:53:57,834 --> 00:54:00,803
He no longer gives up
his own identity...

933
00:54:00,837 --> 00:54:04,329
to be a safe part
of his surroundings.

934
00:54:04,374 --> 00:54:06,342
His taste wasn't terrible.

935
00:54:06,376 --> 00:54:09,345
He was a man who preferred
watching baseball...

936
00:54:09,379 --> 00:54:11,347
to reading "Moby Dick"...

937
00:54:11,381 --> 00:54:14,839
and that got him off
on the wrong foot...

938
00:54:14,884 --> 00:54:16,852
or so the legend goes.

939
00:54:16,886 --> 00:54:19,354
It was much more
a matter of symbolism.

940
00:54:19,389 --> 00:54:22,358
To the Marxists
he was one thing.

941
00:54:22,392 --> 00:54:24,860
The Catholic Church
never forgave him...

942
00:54:24,894 --> 00:54:26,361
for the Vatican incident.

943
00:54:26,396 --> 00:54:27,863
The American people...

944
00:54:27,897 --> 00:54:31,355
in the throes of the Depression
as they were...

945
00:54:31,401 --> 00:54:34,370
found in him a symbol
of possibility...

946
00:54:34,404 --> 00:54:36,804
of self-improvement
and self-fulfillment.

947
00:54:36,840 --> 00:54:39,809
And of course,
the Freudians had a ball.

948
00:54:39,843 --> 00:54:43,301
They could interpret him
in any way they pleased.

949
00:54:43,346 --> 00:54:45,314
It was all symbolism...

950
00:54:45,348 --> 00:54:49,409
but no two intellectuals
agreed about what it meant.

951
00:54:49,452 --> 00:54:52,012
I don't know if you can call it
a triumph of psychotherapy.

952
00:54:52,055 --> 00:54:55,024
It's more like a triumph
of aesthetic instincts.

953
00:54:55,058 --> 00:54:57,526
Dr. Fletcher's techniques
didn't owe anything...

954
00:54:57,560 --> 00:55:00,028
to then-current schools
of therapy...

955
00:55:00,063 --> 00:55:03,521
but she sensed what was needed
and provided it.

956
00:55:03,566 --> 00:55:05,534
That was, in its way...

957
00:55:05,568 --> 00:55:07,593
a remarkable
creative accomplishment.

958
00:55:07,637 --> 00:55:10,197
When I think about it,
it seems to me his story...

959
00:55:10,240 --> 00:55:13,698
reflected a lot of the
Jewish experience in America...

960
00:55:13,743 --> 00:55:18,203
the great urge to push in
and to find one's place...

961
00:55:18,248 --> 00:55:21,217
and then to assimilate
into the culture.

962
00:55:21,251 --> 00:55:23,913
He wanted to assimilate
like crazy.

963
00:55:31,594 --> 00:55:34,722
Eudora Fletcher's
life has also changed...

964
00:55:34,764 --> 00:55:36,231
from this experience.

965
00:55:36,266 --> 00:55:39,235
For her, fame and recognition
are empty rewards...

966
00:55:39,269 --> 00:55:42,727
and do not live up
to the adolescent fantasies...

967
00:55:42,772 --> 00:55:45,002
that prompted her ambition.

968
00:55:45,041 --> 00:55:47,976
She and her patient
have fallen in love...

969
00:55:48,011 --> 00:55:50,980
and it is no surprise
when she forsakes...

970
00:55:51,014 --> 00:55:52,982
the upwardly-mobile
attorney Koslow...

971
00:55:53,016 --> 00:55:56,179
and announces wedding plans
with Zelig.

972
00:56:50,540 --> 00:56:54,636
It was wonderful to see
my sister and Leonard together.

973
00:56:54,677 --> 00:56:58,135
She drew strength from him.

974
00:56:58,181 --> 00:57:02,641
And they were so much in love
with each other...

975
00:57:02,685 --> 00:57:07,145
and she looked happier
than she had in years.

976
00:57:07,190 --> 00:57:12,651
I remember they decided
to get married in the spring...

977
00:57:12,695 --> 00:57:16,688
and then, of course,
the roof fell in.

978
00:57:18,268 --> 00:57:20,293
Two weeks before the wedding...

979
00:57:20,336 --> 00:57:23,635
an ex-showgirl
named Lita Fox comes forth...

980
00:57:23,673 --> 00:57:27,131
and claims that
she is married to Zelig.

981
00:57:27,177 --> 00:57:30,635
She also claims
to have had his child.

982
00:57:30,680 --> 00:57:33,672
It is an immediate scandal.

983
00:57:36,820 --> 00:57:38,879
We were married a year ago.

984
00:57:38,922 --> 00:57:43,382
He said he was an actor.
He sounded just like one.

985
00:57:43,426 --> 00:57:45,394
I'm in show business, too.

986
00:57:45,428 --> 00:57:48,397
We drove to Baltimore,
and we were married...

987
00:57:48,431 --> 00:57:51,161
and I have a license
to prove it.

988
00:57:51,201 --> 00:57:54,659
He had married her while under
a different personality.

989
00:57:54,704 --> 00:57:57,172
When she read of the plans...

990
00:57:57,207 --> 00:57:59,175
for his forthcoming wedding
to Eudora Fletcher...

991
00:57:59,209 --> 00:58:02,736
she was mortified and
decided to take legal action.

992
00:58:02,779 --> 00:58:05,680
Zelig says he will
fight it in court...

993
00:58:05,715 --> 00:58:09,981
but public opinion begins
subtly to shift away from him.

994
00:58:10,019 --> 00:58:14,149
Clever attorneys portray
Lita Fox as an abandoned woman.

995
00:58:14,190 --> 00:58:18,627
The child is neglected, poor,
and fatherless.

996
00:58:18,661 --> 00:58:21,596
Zelig has sold his life story
to Hollywood...

997
00:58:21,631 --> 00:58:24,031
for a large sum of money.

998
00:58:24,067 --> 00:58:26,092
When the scandal breaks...

999
00:58:26,135 --> 00:58:28,603
the studio demands
its money back.

1000
00:58:28,638 --> 00:58:31,937
Zelig can only return half.
The rest has been spent.

1001
00:58:31,975 --> 00:58:35,411
Outraged, the studio gives him
half his life back.

1002
00:58:35,445 --> 00:58:37,413
They keep the best moments.

1003
00:58:37,447 --> 00:58:41,907
He is left with only his
sleeping hours and mealtimes.

1004
00:58:41,951 --> 00:58:46,445
Zelig is shaken by the scandal,
but it is only the beginning.

1005
00:58:46,489 --> 00:58:48,480
Now another woman
steps forward.

1006
00:58:48,525 --> 00:58:52,655
Helen Gray, a salesgirl
from a Wisconsin gift shop...

1007
00:58:52,695 --> 00:58:56,153
claims that Zelig
is the father of her twins.

1008
00:58:56,199 --> 00:59:01,159
She tells lawyers that he passed
himself off as a fur trapper.

1009
00:59:01,204 --> 00:59:03,672
Zelig has no recollection,
but admits...

1010
00:59:03,706 --> 00:59:07,665
it could have happened
during one of his spells.

1011
00:59:07,710 --> 00:59:09,837
It's the signal
for the floodgates to open.

1012
00:59:09,879 --> 00:59:13,474
He married me
at the First Church of Harlem.

1013
00:59:13,516 --> 00:59:16,314
He told me he was the brother
of Duke Ellington.

1014
00:59:16,352 --> 00:59:19,844
He was the guy
who smashed my car up.

1015
00:59:19,889 --> 00:59:21,857
It was brand-new.

1016
00:59:21,891 --> 00:59:24,860
Then he backed up
over my mother's wrist.

1017
00:59:24,894 --> 00:59:29,854
She's elderly
and uses her wrist a lot.

1018
00:59:29,899 --> 00:59:32,834
He painted my house
a disgusting color.

1019
00:59:32,869 --> 00:59:35,337
He said he was a painter.

1020
00:59:35,371 --> 00:59:38,101
I couldn't believe the results.

1021
00:59:38,141 --> 00:59:40,735
Then he disappeared.

1022
00:59:40,777 --> 00:59:42,768
That Zelig
could be responsible...

1023
00:59:42,812 --> 00:59:45,781
for the behavior of
each personality he assumed...

1024
00:59:45,815 --> 00:59:48,477
means dozens of lawsuits.

1025
00:59:48,518 --> 00:59:50,952
He is sued
for bigamy, adultery...

1026
00:59:50,987 --> 00:59:53,956
automobile accidents,
plagiarism, household damages...

1027
00:59:53,990 --> 00:59:56,618
negligence, property damages...

1028
00:59:56,659 --> 01:00:00,220
and performing unnecessary
dental extractions.

1029
01:00:00,263 --> 01:00:03,289
I would like to apologize
to everyone.

1030
01:00:03,333 --> 01:00:06,302
I'm awfully sorry
for marrying all those women.

1031
01:00:06,336 --> 01:00:08,304
It just... I don't know.

1032
01:00:08,338 --> 01:00:11,307
It just seemed
like the thing to do.

1033
01:00:11,341 --> 01:00:14,310
To the gentleman
whose appendix I took out...

1034
01:00:14,344 --> 01:00:16,812
I don't know what to say.

1035
01:00:16,846 --> 01:00:18,814
If it's any consolation...

1036
01:00:18,848 --> 01:00:21,316
I may still have it
somewhere around the house.

1037
01:00:21,351 --> 01:00:25,811
My deepest apology goes to
the Trokman family in Detroit.

1038
01:00:25,855 --> 01:00:29,313
I never delivered
a baby before in my life...

1039
01:00:29,359 --> 01:00:34,763
and I just thought that
ice tongs was the way to do it.

1040
01:00:34,797 --> 01:00:38,597
Thriving mercilessly on
loopholes and technicalities...

1041
01:00:38,635 --> 01:00:42,264
the American legal profession
has a field day.

1042
01:00:42,305 --> 01:00:44,273
Zelig is branded a criminal.

1043
01:00:44,307 --> 01:00:47,276
Despite Dr. Fletcher's
insistence that he cannot be...

1044
01:00:47,310 --> 01:00:50,939
held responsible for actions
while in his chameleon state...

1045
01:00:50,980 --> 01:00:52,413
it is no use.

1046
01:00:52,448 --> 01:00:56,578
Leonard Zelig sets
a bad moral influence.

1047
01:00:56,619 --> 01:00:59,588
America is a moral country.

1048
01:00:59,622 --> 01:01:03,422
It's a God-fearing country.

1049
01:01:03,459 --> 01:01:10,160
We don't condone scandals...
scandals of fraud and polygamy.

1050
01:01:10,199 --> 01:01:16,934
In keeping with a pure society,
I say, lynch the little Hebe.

1051
01:01:18,007 --> 01:01:19,975
Throughout
the humiliating ordeal...

1052
01:01:20,009 --> 01:01:24,639
Eudora Fletcher stands by
the man she loves, valiantly.

1053
01:01:24,681 --> 01:01:26,649
Privately, she tells friends...

1054
01:01:26,683 --> 01:01:29,652
that she is worried about
Zelig's emotional condition...

1055
01:01:29,686 --> 01:01:32,655
which seems to her
to be deteriorating...

1056
01:01:32,689 --> 01:01:36,022
under the weight
of conservative moral opinion.

1057
01:01:36,059 --> 01:01:38,960
In public, he tries to keep up
an appearance of composure...

1058
01:01:38,995 --> 01:01:40,895
but it is increasingly
difficult.

1059
01:01:40,930 --> 01:01:44,024
It is clear that
he is coming apart...

1060
01:01:44,067 --> 01:01:47,525
when he and Eudora dine
at a Greek restaurant...

1061
01:01:47,570 --> 01:01:52,633
and in the midst of the meal,
Zelig begins to turn Greek.

1062
01:01:57,647 --> 01:02:00,616
He longs desperately
to be liked once again...

1063
01:02:00,650 --> 01:02:03,585
to be accepted, to fit in.

1064
01:02:03,619 --> 01:02:06,884
Public clamor over his morality
reaches a fever pitch...

1065
01:02:06,923 --> 01:02:09,892
and on the eve
of his sentencing...

1066
01:02:09,926 --> 01:02:12,156
Leonard Zelig vanishes.

1067
01:02:19,102 --> 01:02:22,833
This is Chief Inspector
of Police Thomas Dowd...

1068
01:02:22,872 --> 01:02:25,432
with a national
broadcasting news break.

1069
01:02:25,475 --> 01:02:27,443
Leonard Zelig is missing.

1070
01:02:27,477 --> 01:02:29,945
On the eve of his sentencing...

1071
01:02:29,979 --> 01:02:33,073
for an assortment
of crimes and misdemeanors...

1072
01:02:33,116 --> 01:02:35,914
ranging from polygamy to fraud,
he has disappeared.

1073
01:02:35,952 --> 01:02:37,920
We are searching for clues...

1074
01:02:37,954 --> 01:02:40,422
and would appreciate
speaking with anyone...

1075
01:02:40,456 --> 01:02:44,256
who might have any information
leading to his apprehension.

1076
01:02:44,293 --> 01:02:47,228
My sister was just shattered.

1077
01:02:47,263 --> 01:02:52,223
She tried to keep up
a calm front...

1078
01:02:52,268 --> 01:02:54,736
but she was just too upset.

1079
01:02:54,771 --> 01:02:56,739
And she wasn't a person...

1080
01:02:56,773 --> 01:02:59,742
who usually
displayed emotion easily...

1081
01:02:59,776 --> 01:03:02,267
except where Leonard
was concerned.

1082
01:03:05,515 --> 01:03:08,746
Dr. Fletcher and the police
confer daily.

1083
01:03:08,785 --> 01:03:10,753
Together they make
public appeals...

1084
01:03:10,787 --> 01:03:13,756
to anyone who might know
of his whereabouts.

1085
01:03:13,790 --> 01:03:16,258
Apart from several
crank telephone calls...

1086
01:03:16,292 --> 01:03:18,123
there is little response.

1087
01:03:18,161 --> 01:03:21,597
Months go by,
and Zelig is not heard from.

1088
01:03:21,631 --> 01:03:23,098
Cars are searched.

1089
01:03:23,132 --> 01:03:25,930
False leads pour in
from everywhere.

1090
01:03:25,968 --> 01:03:28,459
His jacket is recovered
in Texas.

1091
01:03:28,504 --> 01:03:31,473
A manhunt in that state
proves futile.

1092
01:03:31,507 --> 01:03:34,840
He is reported seen
in Chicago, in California.

1093
01:03:34,877 --> 01:03:38,711
This still photo appears
to have a man resembling him...

1094
01:03:38,748 --> 01:03:41,239
with a mariachi band in Mexico.

1095
01:03:44,720 --> 01:03:47,746
Dr. Fletcher continues
to search for Zelig...

1096
01:03:47,790 --> 01:03:50,759
but hopes fade
with each passing day.

1097
01:03:50,793 --> 01:03:54,251
All I could think of
was Leonard...

1098
01:03:54,297 --> 01:03:57,266
how much I missed him
and loved him...

1099
01:03:57,300 --> 01:04:00,269
and all the terrific times
we'd spent together.

1100
01:04:00,303 --> 01:04:03,966
It was really
a very painful time for me.

1101
01:04:04,006 --> 01:04:08,500
The year ends,
and Zelig is still missing.

1102
01:04:11,881 --> 01:04:14,315
I just moped around and wept.

1103
01:04:14,350 --> 01:04:17,319
And one night
after a very bad time...

1104
01:04:17,353 --> 01:04:19,821
my sister Meryl said to me...

1105
01:04:19,856 --> 01:04:22,825
"Come on, let's go out
for dinner or a concert."

1106
01:04:22,859 --> 01:04:26,818
I said, "No. I can't do it,"
but she insisted.

1107
01:04:26,863 --> 01:04:30,196
We went out
and ended up in a movie.

1108
01:04:30,233 --> 01:04:33,862
We saw "Grand Hotel," and
with it, there was a newsreel.

1109
01:04:43,746 --> 01:04:46,738
Adolf Hitler and
the National Socialist Party...

1110
01:04:46,782 --> 01:04:49,751
continue to consolidate gains
in depression-ridden Berlin.

1111
01:04:49,785 --> 01:04:52,083
Denouncing
the Treaty of Versailles...

1112
01:04:52,121 --> 01:04:55,852
the Nazis make fervent appeals
to German patriotism...

1113
01:04:55,892 --> 01:04:59,760
Eudora Fletcher is stunned
by what she sees.

1114
01:04:59,795 --> 01:05:01,763
Amongst the brown shirts...

1115
01:05:01,797 --> 01:05:04,766
she spots a figure
who could be Zelig.

1116
01:05:04,800 --> 01:05:08,258
Then it made all
the sense in the world...

1117
01:05:08,304 --> 01:05:11,273
because although
he wanted to be loved...

1118
01:05:11,307 --> 01:05:13,275
craved to be loved...

1119
01:05:13,309 --> 01:05:15,777
there was also
something in him...

1120
01:05:15,811 --> 01:05:19,907
that desired immersion
in the mass and anonymity.

1121
01:05:19,949 --> 01:05:23,214
And Fascism offered Zelig
that kind of opportunity...

1122
01:05:23,252 --> 01:05:27,712
so that he could make something
anonymous of himself...

1123
01:05:27,757 --> 01:05:32,421
by belonging
to this vast movement.

1124
01:05:32,461 --> 01:05:35,953
She sails for
Europe the following week.

1125
01:05:35,998 --> 01:05:38,967
Ten days later,
she arrives in Berlin.

1126
01:05:39,001 --> 01:05:43,461
Germany is a country deep
in the throes of the Depression.

1127
01:05:43,506 --> 01:05:47,033
Militarism and unrest
are in the air.

1128
01:05:47,076 --> 01:05:49,601
She searches everywhere
and makes inquiries...

1129
01:05:49,645 --> 01:05:51,135
but it is impossible.

1130
01:05:51,180 --> 01:05:52,579
After three weeks...

1131
01:05:52,615 --> 01:05:55,083
the authorities begin
to get suspicious.

1132
01:05:55,117 --> 01:05:56,584
They watch her.

1133
01:05:56,619 --> 01:06:00,077
While she is out,
they search her hotel room.

1134
01:06:00,122 --> 01:06:02,056
A fourth week goes by...

1135
01:06:02,091 --> 01:06:04,491
and she is about
to give up and go home...

1136
01:06:04,527 --> 01:06:08,987
when news of a large rally
at Munich catches her attention.

1137
01:06:09,031 --> 01:06:10,999
It is rumored
that it will be...

1138
01:06:11,033 --> 01:06:14,002
the largest gathering to date
of Nazi personnel.

1139
01:06:14,036 --> 01:06:16,334
Eudora Fletcher
is counting on the hope...

1140
01:06:16,372 --> 01:06:21,605
that Zelig may attend and that
if she can confront him...

1141
01:06:21,644 --> 01:06:26,274
the strong feeling he has always
had for her can be awakened.

1142
01:06:26,315 --> 01:06:28,806
At first, all appears hopeless.

1143
01:06:28,851 --> 01:06:30,842
The crowd is huge.

1144
01:06:30,886 --> 01:06:34,481
It seems impossible to locate
any one particular face.

1145
01:06:49,305 --> 01:06:52,274
Then suddenly, a figure flanking
the chancellor...

1146
01:06:52,308 --> 01:06:54,003
catches her attention.

1147
01:06:54,043 --> 01:06:58,673
Behind and to the right
of Hitler, she spots Zelig.

1148
01:06:58,714 --> 01:07:02,775
Struggling to make contact,
she manages to catch his eye.

1149
01:07:02,818 --> 01:07:07,312
Like a man emerging
from a dream, Zelig notices her.

1150
01:07:07,356 --> 01:07:11,816
In a matter of seconds,
everything comes back to him.

1151
01:08:10,252 --> 01:08:12,812
It was nothing like
it happened in the movie.

1152
01:08:12,855 --> 01:08:17,417
When Leonard left the podium,
they didn't know what to think.

1153
01:08:17,460 --> 01:08:19,485
We couldn't believe our eyes.

1154
01:08:19,528 --> 01:08:21,496
Hitler's speech was ruined.

1155
01:08:21,530 --> 01:08:25,330
He wanted to make
a good joke about Poland...

1156
01:08:25,367 --> 01:08:29,827
but just then,
Zelig interfered...

1157
01:08:29,872 --> 01:08:33,831
and Hitler was extremely upset.

1158
01:08:33,876 --> 01:08:39,781
The SS wanted to grab Zelig...

1159
01:08:39,815 --> 01:08:42,784
but if they would have
grabbed him...

1160
01:08:42,818 --> 01:08:45,787
they probably would have
tortured him...

1161
01:08:45,821 --> 01:08:48,289
or maybe even shot him.

1162
01:08:48,324 --> 01:08:49,791
So in the confusion...

1163
01:08:49,825 --> 01:08:53,283
Fletcher and Zelig
got out of the building...

1164
01:08:53,329 --> 01:08:55,297
through a side door.

1165
01:08:55,331 --> 01:08:58,789
They grabbed a car,
sped away in the car...

1166
01:08:58,834 --> 01:09:01,667
and the SS after them,
shot them.

1167
01:09:02,705 --> 01:09:04,730
In rare
German newsreel footage...

1168
01:09:04,773 --> 01:09:07,765
a quick glimpse of the escape
was recorded.

1169
01:09:21,790 --> 01:09:24,759
I was flying.
It was wonderful.

1170
01:09:24,793 --> 01:09:27,261
And then suddenly,
something happened.

1171
01:09:27,296 --> 01:09:29,764
I was frightened.
I lost control.

1172
01:09:29,798 --> 01:09:31,766
We went into a dive.

1173
01:09:31,800 --> 01:09:36,032
Leonard was so terrified that
he changed his personality...

1174
01:09:36,071 --> 01:09:40,030
and before my eyes,
because I was a pilot...

1175
01:09:40,075 --> 01:09:42,270
he turned into one, too.

1176
01:09:42,311 --> 01:09:45,075
Zelig takes control
of the airplane.

1177
01:09:45,114 --> 01:09:47,082
Acting the role of pilot...

1178
01:09:47,116 --> 01:09:49,676
he struggles valiantly
with the aircraft.

1179
01:09:49,718 --> 01:09:53,745
The Germans, who are stunned,
take a full fifteen minutes...

1180
01:09:53,789 --> 01:09:56,622
before following
in hot pursuit of their quarry.

1181
01:09:56,659 --> 01:09:58,752
With Eudora Fletcher
unconscious...

1182
01:09:58,794 --> 01:10:01,763
Zelig, who had never flown
before in his life...

1183
01:10:01,797 --> 01:10:04,265
not only escapes
the German pilots...

1184
01:10:04,300 --> 01:10:08,259
but sets a record for flying
nonstop across the Atlantic...

1185
01:10:08,304 --> 01:10:09,794
upside down.

1186
01:10:30,960 --> 01:10:33,394
With a storm of cheers
and a blizzard of ticker tape...

1187
01:10:33,429 --> 01:10:36,227
New York welcomes back
Eudora Fletcher...

1188
01:10:36,265 --> 01:10:38,893
and Leonard Zelig,
the human chameleon.

1189
01:10:38,934 --> 01:10:42,927
His remarkable feat of aviation
fills the nation with pride...

1190
01:10:42,972 --> 01:10:45,600
and earns him
a full presidential pardon.

1191
01:10:45,641 --> 01:10:47,302
Forgiving multitudes
flock to see him...

1192
01:10:47,343 --> 01:10:50,278
as he sits by the side
of his plucky bride-to-be.

1193
01:10:50,312 --> 01:10:52,371
Their journey of triumph
leads to City Hall.

1194
01:10:52,414 --> 01:10:55,383
New York's greatest honor,
the Medal of Valor...

1195
01:10:55,417 --> 01:10:58,386
is bestowed on Zelig
by Carter Dean.

1196
01:10:58,420 --> 01:11:03,357
You are a great inspiration
to the young of this nation...

1197
01:11:03,392 --> 01:11:05,860
who will one day grow up...

1198
01:11:05,894 --> 01:11:08,863
and be great doctors
and great patients.

1199
01:11:16,905 --> 01:11:18,873
This was a great thrill.

1200
01:11:18,907 --> 01:11:21,876
I'm glad we lived
to see this day.

1201
01:11:21,910 --> 01:11:24,879
Right. I've never flown
before in my life...

1202
01:11:24,913 --> 01:11:27,882
and it shows exactly
what you can do...

1203
01:11:27,916 --> 01:11:29,907
if you're a total psychotic.

1204
01:11:34,757 --> 01:11:37,157
The thing was paradoxical...

1205
01:11:37,192 --> 01:11:40,650
because what enabled him to
perform this astounding feat...

1206
01:11:40,696 --> 01:11:44,325
was his ability
to transform himself.

1207
01:11:44,366 --> 01:11:49,326
Therefore, his sickness was also
at the root of his salvation...

1208
01:11:49,371 --> 01:11:53,330
and I think it's interesting
to view the thing that way.

1209
01:11:53,375 --> 01:11:59,473
It was his very disorder
that made a hero of him.

1210
01:11:59,515 --> 01:12:02,575
It was really absurd in a way.

1211
01:12:02,618 --> 01:12:05,587
I mean, he had
this curious quirk...

1212
01:12:05,621 --> 01:12:07,418
this strange characteristic.

1213
01:12:07,456 --> 01:12:09,924
And for a time,
everyone loved him...

1214
01:12:09,958 --> 01:12:12,426
and then people
stopped loving him.

1215
01:12:12,461 --> 01:12:15,430
Then he did this stunt
with the airplane...

1216
01:12:15,464 --> 01:12:17,932
and then everybody
loved him again.

1217
01:12:17,966 --> 01:12:20,935
And that was what
the twenties were like.

1218
01:12:20,969 --> 01:12:24,666
When you think about it,
has America changed so much?

1219
01:12:24,707 --> 01:12:26,675
I don't think so.

1220
01:12:26,709 --> 01:12:31,339
After untangling
countless legal details...

1221
01:12:31,380 --> 01:12:34,838
Leonard Zelig
and Eudora Fletcher marry.

1222
01:12:34,883 --> 01:12:39,115
It is a simple ceremony
captured on home movies.

1223
01:12:57,973 --> 01:13:02,103
"Wanting only to be liked,
he distorted himself...

1224
01:13:02,144 --> 01:13:04,772
"beyond measure,"
wrote Scott Fitzgerald.

1225
01:13:04,813 --> 01:13:07,941
"One wonders what would have
happened if at the outset...

1226
01:13:07,983 --> 01:13:12,943
"he had had the courage to speak
his mind and not pretend.

1227
01:13:12,988 --> 01:13:17,084
"In the end, it was, after all,
not the approbation of many...

1228
01:13:17,126 --> 01:13:21,961
"but the love of one woman
that changed his life."